What can I say but yum?! This is a perfect holiday dish and great for winter. I got a huge, unidentifiable squash from my CSA and used it for this - it worked out great! It turned out to be similar to butternut squash. The caramelized onions to top took forever to cook, but were totally worth it.

Rating: 3
This recipe was delicious! We modified some of the amounts, and I think it worked perfectly: 1 or 2 onions at most 1/8 cup sugar (used purevia instead) 1/5 tsp cinnamon 1/4 cup raisins (didn't plump them) Will definitely make again! YUM!

