Rating: 3
It was superb! I loved the mixture of flavors. It reminded me of a Sephardic tsimmes, if there is such a thing. I used the Spanish squash, called calabasa, which in Israel is often mistakenly called pumpkin. I'm looking forward to making it again for company. It would be a very appropriate side dish for Thanksgiving or just about any Jewish holiday including Passover.

